<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="section section--cream">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <div class="section-heading reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Common Questions</span>
      <h2>Independent Living — FAQs</h2>
    </div>

    <details class="reveal" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-line); padding: var(--space-4) 0;">
      <summary style="cursor:pointer; font-weight:600; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.2rem;">Is independent living right for me if I don&rsquo;t need any care?</summary>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-3);">Yes — that&rsquo;s exactly who independent living is designed for. You manage your own life, come and go freely, and simply enjoy the amenities and community around you. There is no care component unless and until you want one. Many residents live independently for years before ever considering a care-level transition.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="reveal" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-line); padding: var(--space-4) 0;">
      <summary style="cursor:pointer; font-weight:600; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.2rem;">Can I transition to assisted living if my needs change?</summary>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-3);">Yes. One of the key advantages of choosing a blended community like Azalea Estates is that assisted care is available on the same campus. If your needs evolve, you can transition to assisted living without moving away from your neighbors, your routines, or the staff who know you.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="reveal" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-line); padding: var(--space-4) 0;">
      <summary style="cursor:pointer; font-weight:600; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.2rem;">Can family members visit and join me for meals?</summary>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-3);">Absolutely. Family members are always welcome to visit, and guest meals in our dining room can be arranged. We also have private dining spaces available for birthdays, holidays, and special occasions.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="reveal" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-line); padding: var(--space-4) 0;">
      <summary style="cursor:pointer; font-weight:600; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.2rem;">Can I personalize my apartment?</summary>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-3);">Yes. Residents are encouraged to bring their own furniture, artwork, and personal touches to make their suite feel like home. Every apartment has ample closet space, a private bath, windows with garden views, and an individually controlled thermostat.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="reveal" style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-line); padding: var(--space-4) 0;">
      <summary style="cursor:pointer; font-weight:600; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.2rem;">Are there activities for residents who want to stay active?</summary>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-3);">Extensively. Our 3,000 sq. ft. wellness center, heated saltwater pool, daily fitness classes, walking paths, community garden, and a full monthly activity calendar ensure that residents who want to stay active have more options than they can keep up with. Nothing is required — everything is available.</p>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FLOOR PLANS PREVIEW -->
